&lt;p&gt;At Mesh, our mission is to enable consumers to pay and be paid with any asset. Today, trillions of dollars in tokenized assets exist but remain largely unusable for everyday commerce. Mesh is bridging this gap by making crypto payments reliable, useful, and ubiquitous. We combine a powerful orchestration engine with a seamless consumer app to unlock liquidity for the world. Backed by leading investors like PayPal Ventures, Paradigm, and Galaxy Ventures, we are building the infrastructure for the next era of the global economy. Join us!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Senior Product Manager to join our &quot;Core&quot; team. This team builds the foundational infrastructure that handles crypto transfers, bridging logic, and network connectivity.&amp;nbsp; Your initial mandate will be to aggressively expand Mesh&#39;s footprint by leading our integration strategy for Centralized Exchanges (CEXs) and Web3 Wallets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here is the truth about what it takes to succeed in this role: you must possess raw intellectual horsepower, a deep pride in the quality of your work, and a relentless, undeniable work ethic.&amp;nbsp; Some Web3 experience is preferred; exceptional execution is mandatory. We will teach you the crypto infrastructure.&amp;nbsp; If you can drop into a highly complex, ambiguous technical domain, figure out how it works, and start driving outcomes immediately, you belong here.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ownership: You are the execution engine for the Core team. If a process is broken, you fix it. If an engineering team is blocked, you unblock them. You take pride in sweating the details that others ignore.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expand the Network: Own the execution for expanding Mesh&#39;s coverage of external platforms. You will figure out how to integrate new crypto exchanges and standardize connections with self-custodial wallets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Architect for Scale: Partner with our Head of Core and senior engineers to ensure that as we add dozens of new connections, our routing logic remains standardized, scalable, and secure. You will write crystal-clear specs and map out edge cases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High Leverage &amp;amp; Efficiency: You ruthlessly optimize and automate your own operational workflows. You treat your time as the company&#39;s most valuable resource, utilizing modern tools (AI, scripts, automations) to scale your output so you can focus on high-impact problem-solving.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cross-Functional Velocity: Collaborate tightly with Engineering and Business Development to prioritize the right integrations and ensure our core connectivity meets the SLAs required by our enterprise clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience: 3+ years of building and shipping hard things. Traditional technical PM experience is preferred but not strictly required.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Intellectual Horsepower: You are a rapid learner who can quickly deconstruct complex systems (APIs, ledgers, financial routing) and explain them simply.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Relentless Drive: You have a demonstrated history of working incredibly hard and caring deeply about the output of your work. You do not wait to be told what to do.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Systems Thinking: You are highly comfortable reading technical documentation, discussing API payloads, and debating architectural tradeoffs with engineers. You don&#39;t need to write code, but you must be able to design systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
